Earthquake activity:

Timber Lakes-area historical earthquake activity is significantly above Utah state average. It is 2053% greater than the overall U.S. average.

On 8/18/1959 at 06:37:13, a magnitude 7.7 (7.7 UK, Class: Major, Intensity: VIII - XII) earthquake occurred 284.5 miles away from the city center, causing $26,000,000 total damage

On 10/3/1915 at 06:52:48, a magnitude 7.6 (7.6 UK) earthquake occurred 328.9 miles away from the city center

On 10/28/1983 at 14:06:06, a magnitude 7.3 (6.2 MB, 7.3 MS, 7.0 MW) earthquake occurred 281.3 miles away from the city center, causing 2 deaths (2 shaking deaths) and 3 injuries, causing $15,000,000 total damage

On 3/28/1975 at 02:31:05, a magnitude 6.2 (6.1 MB, 6.0 MS, 6.2 ML, Class: Strong, Intensity: VII - IX) earthquake occurred 124.0 miles away from the city center

On 3/18/2020 at 13:09:31, a magnitude 5.7 (5.7 MW, Depth: 7.4 mi, Class: Moderate, Intensity: VI - VII) earthquake occurred 47.6 miles away from Timber Lakes center

On 12/21/1932 at 06:10:09, a magnitude 7.2 (7.2 UK) earthquake occurred 389.3 miles away from Timber Lakes center
